Bitcoin peers scanner

X-Ray is an open-source tool written in Go for real-time scanning of Bitcoin peers. 

Features
- resolves seed nodes via DNS, 
- connects to nodes, performs handshake dance (version, verack, ping), 
- retrieves more node addresses from peers, 


Environment variables
DEBUG=1 - enables debug mode logging (by default logging level is info)
GUI=0 - disables GUI (by default GUI is enabled)
TESTNET=1 - enables testnet mode (by default mainnet is used)

Docs
https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Protocol_documentation


